Technical Appendices

Appendix A: Mathematical Formulation of Wu Xing Dynamics

The state of an ELEMENTS OS system can be represented as:

```
S(t) = [w, f, e, m, v] ∈ ℝ⁵
```

Where:

· w = Wood strength
· f = Fire strength
· e = Earth strength
· m = Metal strength
· v = Water strength

The system evolves according to:

```
S(t+1) = α·S(t) + β·G·S(t) - γ·K·S(t) + δ·I(t) + ε·N(0,σ)
```

Where:

· G = Generating matrix (nourishment relationships)
· K = Controlling matrix (regulation relationships)
· I(t) = External inputs
· N(0,σ) = Stochastic noise

Appendix B: Elemental Classification Algorithm

```
function classify_process(process):
    characteristics = analyze_process(process)
    
    wood_score = characteristics.growth * 0.3 + 
                 characteristics.planning * 0.4 +
                 characteristics.flexibility * 0.3
    
    fire_score = characteristics.energy * 0.4 +
                 characteristics.transformation * 0.4 +
                 characteristics.speed * 0.2
    
    earth_score = characteristics.stability * 0.4 +
                  characteristics.storage * 0.3 +
                  characteristics.support * 0.3
    
    metal_score = characteristics.precision * 0.4 +
                  characteristics.structure * 0.3 +
                  characteristics.efficiency * 0.3
    
    water_score = characteristics.flow * 0.4 +
                  characteristics.adaptation * 0.4 +
                  characteristics.persistence * 0.2
    
    scores = [wood_score, fire_score, earth_score, 
              metal_score, water_score]
    
    return element_with_max_score(scores)
```

Appendix C: Qi Flow Calculation

```
function calculate_qi_flow(source, destination, system_state):
    # Base flow from source strength
    base_flow = system_state[source] * 0.1
    
    # Generating boost if source generates destination
    if is_generating(source, destination):
        base_flow *= 1.3
    
    # Controlling reduction if source controls destination  
    if is_controlling(source, destination):
        base_flow *= 0.8
    
    # System-wide balance consideration
    balance_factor = 1.0 - abs(system_state[source] - 
                              system_state[destination]) * 0.5
    
    return base_flow * balance_factor
```

Appendix D: Hardware Compatibility Matrix

